#: ../../../firmware-guide/acpi/namespace.rst:26
msgid "ACPI Definition Blocks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../firmware-guide/acpi/namespace.rst:28
msgid ""
"The ACPI firmware sets up RSDP (Root System Description Pointer) in the "
"system memory address space pointing to the XSDT (Extended System "
"Description Table).  The XSDT always points to the FADT (Fixed ACPI "
"Description Table) using its first entry, the data within the FADT includes "
"various fixed-length entries that describe fixed ACPI features of the "
"hardware.  The FADT contains a pointer to the DSDT (Differentiated System "
"Description Table).  The XSDT also contains entries pointing to possibly "
"multiple SSDTs (Secondary System Description Table)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../firmware-guide/acpi/namespace.rst:38
msgid ""
"The DSDT and SSDT data is organized in data structures called definition "
"blocks that contain definitions of various objects, including ACPI control "
"methods, encoded in AML (ACPI Machine Language).  The data block of the DSDT "
"along with the contents of SSDTs represents a hierarchical data structure "
"called the ACPI namespace whose topology reflects the structure of the "
"underlying hardware platform."
msgstr ""

